<DOC><DOCNO> AP880817-0285 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-17-88 0156EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f PM-OilPrices     08-17 0199</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Oil Prices,0206</SECOND><HEAD>Oil Futures Prices Decline Ahead of Tuesday API Report</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Oil futures were weaker in quiet markets aheadof an American Petroleum Institute report indicating a decline incrude oil stocks during the past week.   On the New York Mercantile Exchange, contracts for Septemberdelivery of West Texas Intermediate, the benchmark grade of U.S.crude oil, fell 12 cents a barrel to close at $15.49 a barrel onTuesday.   Refined products traded on the exchange also rose. Contracts forSeptember delivery of wholesale heating oil decreased 0.24 cent tofinish at 44.03 cents a gallon, while September gasoline slipped0.26 cent to 46.11 a gallon.   Crude oil futures opened the day stronger than expected in thindealings, then eased off as traders awaited the American PetroleumInstitute's weekly report on oil inventories, analysts said.   The report, released after the market closed, showed crude oilstocks fll by 3.6 million barrels, gasoline inventories rose 1.5million barrels and distillate stocks rose 1.4 million barrels inthe past week.   Reports that ministers from the Organization of PetroleumExporting Countries were talking of a November meeting did littleto spur Tuesday's energy prices, analysts said.</TEXT></DOC>